# {{finance}} The practice of a [[stockbroker]], when they receive a large [[client]] order, placing an order for their own [[account]] ahead of the client's, knowing when the client's is placed it will move the [[market]] and create a [[profit]] for the broker.
# {{finance}} The practice of a [[stockbroker]] placing orders for their own [[account]] in a stock they are about to [[recommend]] to clients.
===Usage notes===
Also spelt '''frontrunning''' or '''front-running'''.